AtlasAnnotation

https://openminds.ebrains.eu/sands/AtlasAnnotation

part of SANDS in version v3 - view as JSON Schema

Required properties are highlighted in bold
propertyvalue
name*descriptiontypeinstruction
criteriaQualityType Distinct class that defines how the judgement or decision was made for a particular criteria. linked object CriteriaQualityType Add the quality type of the stated criteria used to define this atlas annotation.
internalIdentifier Term or code that identifies someone or something within a particular product. string Enter the identifier used for this annotation within the file it is stored in.
bestViewPoint Coordinate point from which you get the best view of something. embedded object CoordinatePoint Add the coordinate point identifying the best view of this atlas annotation in space.
criteria Aspects or standards on which a judgement or decision is based. linked object ProtocolExecution Add the protocol execution defining the criteria that were applied to produce this atlas annotation.
displayColor Preferred coloring. string Enter the preferred display color (HEX) for this atlas annotation.
inspiredBy Reference to an inspiring element. linked object array (1 - n) of type:
File 		Add one or several (source) files that inspired the definition of this atlas annotation.
laterality Differentiation between a pair of lateral homologous parts of the body. linked object array (1 - 2) of type:
Laterality 		Add one or both sides of the body, bilateral organ or bilateral organ part that this atlas annotation is defined in.
lookupLabel string Enter a lookup label for this atlas annotation that may help you to more easily find it again.
visualizedIn Reference to an image in which something is visible. linked object File Add the (source) image file in which this atlas annotation is visualized in.
*This is the simplified property name - within a metadata instance of this schema (JSON-LD) the properties are extended to map to the openMINDS vocabulary namespace ("https://openminds.ebrains.eu/vocab/PROPERTY_NAME").
